To compile wmjump you need the some development packages installed on your system. For example, on Debian you have to execute:

    sudo aptitude install build-essential libx11-dev libxmu-dev libglib2.0-dev libgtk2.0-dev libcairo2-dev libgdk-pixbuf2.0-dev libatk1.0-dev 

In order to build wmjump, execute:

    ./build.sh

The installation consists of simply copying files:

    [ -d ~/.wmjump/ ] || { mkdir ~/.wmjump/ ; cp data/*  ~/.wmjump/ ; }
    sudo install -g root -o root -m 0755 wmjump /usr/bin/
    sudo install -g root -o root -m 0644 wmjump.1 /usr/share/man/man1/

The instructions for use and config of wmjump can be found in README or by running:

    man wmjump


